.TH "KRYOFLUXUI" "1" "" "KryoFlux 3.50" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
kryofluxui - KryoFlux graphical user interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]kryofluxui\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]kryofluxui\f[R] launches the KryoFlux graphical user interface, a
Java-based multi-platform application that provides a visual front-end
to \f[B]dtc\f[R](1), the KryoFlux Disk Tool Console.
.PP
The GUI covers the most common KryoFlux operations and is recommended
for users who are not familiar with the command line.
Any action performed through the GUI is ultimately translated into
\f[B]dtc\f[R] command-line calls; every feature available in the GUI is
therefore also accessible programmatically via \f[B]dtc\f[R] directly.
.PP
The main window is organised into three areas:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Track grid\f[R] (upper left): 84 blocks representing the track
positions on the disk surface.
Colour coding indicates the result of each dumped track: green = decoded
without errors, grey = noise or unknown encoding, red = errors found
(retrying), yellow = warnings or additional header data, glowing = track
currently being processed.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Track info\f[R] (upper right): displays detailed information for
the selected track, with tabs for \f[B]Histogram\f[R] and
\f[B]Scatter\f[R] views (available for STREAM format only).
In the scatter view, keys \f[B]F1\f[R]\[en]\f[B]F5\f[R] select a
revolution, \f[B]a\f[R] animates revolutions,
\f[B]r\f[R]/\f[B]Shift-r\f[R] adjusts the display RPM by ±5, and
\f[B]i\f[R] toggles the info overlay.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]Control section\f[R] (lower area): shows the current track, drive
controls, output filename, format selector, and status line.
.SS Profiles
.PP
The format selector relies on \f[I]profiles\f[R].
A profile is a named set of \f[B]dtc\f[R] parameters describing how a
disk should be dumped.
Profiles can be cloned and customised.
Multiple profiles can be active simultaneously by choosing
\f[B]<multiple>\f[R] in the format selector, enabling combined outputs
such as STREAM files alongside a decoded AmigaDOS ADF in a single pass.
.SS Requirements
.PP
\f[B]kryofluxui\f[R] requires Java 8 (OpenJDK 8 or later, or Eclipse
Temurin).
The \f[B]dtc\f[R] package must also be installed and the KryoFlux
hardware must be set up beforehand (see \f[B]dtc\f[R](1) and the full
manual in \f[V]/usr/share/doc/dtc-doc/\f[R]).
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
All options are passed directly to the underlying Java Virtual Machine
or to \f[B]dtc\f[R].
Refer to the KryoFlux manual for GUI-specific profile configuration.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[V]/usr/share/kryoflux/kryoflux-ui.jar\f[R]
KryoFlux GUI Java archive.
.TP
\f[V]/usr/share/applications/kryofluxui.desktop\f[R]
Desktop entry for application menu integration.
.TP
\f[V]/usr/share/icons/hicolor/128x128/apps/kryofluxui.png\f[R]
Application icon.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]dtc\f[R](1)
.PP
Full documentation: \f[V]/usr/share/doc/dtc-doc/\f[R]
